16 child custody cases, is amended in subsection (a) by revising paragraphs (12) and (13) and
17 by adding a new paragraph to read as follows:
18 "(12) All judgments or orders entered pursuant to Code Section 35-3-37; and
19 (13) All judgments or orders entered pursuant to Code Section 9-11-11.1; and
20 (14) All judgments, orders, or rulings in civil actions granting or denying or refusing to
21 grant or deny immunity to one or more parties based upon sovereign, municipal, official,
22 qualified, legislative, or judicial immunity established by the United States Constitution
23 or the Constitution, laws, or common law of this state shall have the right of direct appeal
24 under this paragraph, and such right shall be exercised within thirty days of any
25 judgment, order, or ruling. The right of direct appeal under this paragraph shall not be
26 exercised by any one party more than once in any civil action. This paragraph shall not
27 preclude taking an appeal pursuant to any other paragraph in this subsection."
28 SECTION 2.
29 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
